<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?> <?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="rss.xsl"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"> <channel> <title>Hector Steenbergen-Cockerton</title><description>Urban Sociology &amp; Energy Transition Researcher</description><link>https://hec-steen.github.io/</link><atom:link href="https://hec-steen.github.io/feed_rss_updated.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /> <managingEditor>Hector Steenbergen-Cockerton</managingEditor><language>en</language> <pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 15:02:08 -0000</pubDate> <lastBuildDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 15:02:08 -0000</lastBuildDate> <ttl>1440</ttl> <generator>MkDocs RSS plugin - v1.18.1</generator> <image> <url>None</url> <title>Hector Steenbergen-Cockerton</title> <link>https://hec-steen.github.io/</link> </image> <item> <title>Rethinking &#39;significance&#39; — Has the p-value overstayed its welcome?</title> <author>Hector Steenbergen-Cockerton</author> <description>&lt;p&gt;In research, the p-value is often treated as the ultimate test of truth. But should all statistical analysis be held to the same statistical standard? &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In this post, I argue that the p-value is too often used as a universal yardstick, regardless of context or consequences. Sometimes, what counts as “enough” evidence depends on the risks and decisions at stake, not just on whether a result falls below an arbitrary threshold.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Is significance just?&#34; src=&#34;https://videos.openai.com/vg-assets/assets%2Ftask_01jzwvhes2f7vs6e1qw9dpfjsr%2F1752241428_img_0.webp?st=2025-07-11T12%3A15%3A11Z&amp;amp;se=2025-07-17T13%3A15%3A11Z&amp;amp;sks=b&amp;amp;skt=2025-07-11T12%3A15%3A11Z&amp;amp;ske=2025-07-17T13%3A15%3A11Z&amp;amp;sktid=a48cca56-e6da-484e-a814-9c849652bcb3&amp;amp;skoid=aa5ddad1-c91a-4f0a-9aca-e20682cc8969&amp;amp;skv=2019-02-02&amp;amp;sv=2018-11-09&amp;amp;sr=b&amp;amp;sp=r&amp;amp;spr=https%2Chttp&amp;amp;sig=Ls0ySDsQcQ2gyn9LvYhWVylTiInT8siN3HzSbDMMY1c%3D&amp;amp;az=oaivgprodscus&#34;&gt;{ width=&#34;600&#34; }&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hec-steen.github.io/blog/rethinking-significance/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 15:01:47 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hec-steen.github.io/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hector Steenbergen-Cockerton</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hec-steen.github.io/blog/rethinking-significance/</guid> </item> </channel> </rss>